45d1242c-bc1a-4b63-a0bb-e4700cac30c7.do_description: To make the output, you have to... imagine that each red shape is 5 cell wide line and 5 cell tall lines. Fill in each of the missing red cell of the shape with light blue to complete the 5x5 shapes.
45d1242c-bc1a-4b63-a0bb-e4700cac30c7.grid_description: The output grid size... same as the input field
45d1242c-bc1a-4b63-a0bb-e4700cac30c7.see_description: In the input, you should see... grey and red shapes on black field

da277829-40ed-4985-8550-dafe02198cef.do_description: To make the output, you have to...fill in gray units in the area that have red units with red blocks to make crosses with 5 vertical and 5 horizontal units that make up each of the crosses
da277829-40ed-4985-8550-dafe02198cef.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same size
da277829-40ed-4985-8550-dafe02198cef.see_description: In the input, you should see....red units on a black and gray background the red units will be used to form crosses

e2af57a4-7bd1-4298-84b9-31e62ba23d6f.do_description: To make the output, you have to... keep everything the same, but add blue squares around the red squares in order to create a row vertically and a row side to side that are overlapping and of the same range.
e2af57a4-7bd1-4298-84b9-31e62ba23d6f.grid_description: The output grid size...should be the same size as the input grid
e2af57a4-7bd1-4298-84b9-31e62ba23d6f.see_description: In the input, you should see...a lot of black and gray squares with 1-3 red patterns in different places throughout the grid
